review_blob: Copper pour from can. Taste is heavy malt, grain, light plum and charred wood. Would have been better if it had a tad bit more booze.
beer_name: Four Peaks Kilt Lifter Scottish Style Ale

review_blob: Golden pour from bottle. Taste is fruit, citrus, malt, pine and hay. Smooth, balanced and nice.
Bottle. Wow, this one is all over the map. Its like drinking the fruit and produce section of the local grocery store in a bottle. Still, not too bad.
Straw colored pour from bottle with foamy head. Taste is bananas, malt, grain and hay. Decent.
Copper colored pour from can. Taste is citrus, hops, pine, wood and hay. Solid IPA.
Reddish colored pour from the bottle. Taste is caramel, malt, wood, grain and light hops.
Copper colored pour from bottle. Taste is grain, hops, malt and citrus. Overall pretty decent.
Golden pour from can. Nice can, not so nice beer. Not bad, just nothing very new or interesting. Taste is water, straw and grain.
Bottle. Taste is hay, corn, grain, hops, barley and dough. Smooth and enjoyable.
Dark pour from bottle. Taste is berries, malt, grain and a hint of dark chocolate. Smooth and solid.
Golden pour from bottle. Taste is citrus, dough, pine, wood and booze. Typical, but solid, IPA.
Dark pour from bottle. Aroma is deep, deep milk chocolate and creamy peanut butter. Taste is exactly the same. Complex and interesting.
Dark pour from the bottle. Taste is dark fruits, bread, caramel, malt and booze.
Copper pour from the bottle. Taste is grain, dough, mild citrus, malt and booze. Warm finish. Nice.
Copper pour from can. Taste is pie spices, malt, brown sugar and a gentle hint of booze. Hell, it got me in the Christmas spirit.
Bottle. Taste is summer fruit, dough, hay, pine and burnt wood, with a gentle booze finish. Nice IPA.
Dark pour from bottle. This one is a lot of fun, almost like drinking a dessert beer, since it tastes just like root beer. Pour some over vanilla ice cream. Nice.
beer_name: Small Town Not Your Fathers Root Beer (5.9%)

review_blob: Copper pour. Taste is pine, dough, resin, wood and grass, with a gentle boozy finish. Well done.
Straw colored pour from bottle. Taste is dough, bubble gum, hay and malt. Complex and interesting.
Copper colored pour from bottle. Taste is summer fruit, booze, pine cones, dough and hops.
On tap at the Hilton Garden Inn in Palm Springs. Taste is pine, hops, citrus, dough and booze. Solid IPA.
Copper colored pour from can. Taste is straw, pine, grain, hops and a hint of malt. Decent session IPA.
Bottle. Taste is baking spices, malt, grain, charred wood and a bit o honey. Smooth drinking and nice.
Copper pour right from the can. Taste is summer citrus, pine, hops, dough and hay. Very well balanced and very good. Well done.
beer_name: Martin House Cellarmans Reserve IPA - Cascade

review_blob: Golden pour right from the can. Taste is a mild blend of hops, mat, grain and barley. Overall better than I expected.
Golden pour from a can. This one is not as bad as most make it sound. It just is what it is. Describe it however you want, it is still a Pale Ale.
Enjoyed right out of the can. Taste is bold flavors of citrus, hops, pine and dough, with a solid finish. Nice.
Bottle. Taste is corn, grain, hops, malt, citrus, wood and pine. Decent, session type of a beer.
Enjoyed right from the can in sunny Tampa. Taste is citrus, dough, pine and hops. Solid IPA.
beer_name: Tampa Bay Old Elephant Foot IPA

review_blob: On tap at 3 stacks BBQ served by the one and only little pup what in the hell is up. Taste is booze, pine and hops. Nice.
beer_name: Odell Myrcenary Double India Pale Ale

review_blob: Bottle. Taste is pine, citrus, wood, summer fruits and a nice hit of booze. Solid IPA.
Bottle. This one is a big, bold IPA. Taste is dough, citrus, pine, charred wood and loads of hops. Solid DIPA.
Tall can served by the very beautiful Mallorie at Iggys in Ogden. Faint taste of hops, wheat, citrus and pine. But who care....Mallorie was HOT!!
Right from the can in Portland. Taste is bitter citrus, grain, hops, pine and wood. Smooth finish. Nice.
Golden pour from can. Taste was light bitterness and loads of funk. Maybe I need to try this one again. I love Oskar Blues beers, but this one was below their typical high standards.
On tap in Portland. Taste is bitter citrus, pine, malt, dough and wood. Gentle, boozy finish. Well done.
On tap at GB. Taste is light citrus, pine, wood, grain, hay and balanced hops. Smooth and easy drinking.
Bottle. Taste is a mixture of hops, malt, citrus, pine and wood. Solid beer, especially for a pale ale.
Bottle. Taste is summer hay, citrus, hops, grain and malt. Nice, gentle finish. Nice.
Bottle. Taste is grain, various hops, malt, hay and a gentle hint of booze. Smooth and easy drinking.
Bottle. Taste is wheat, corn, grain, hay and barley, with a heathy dose of water. Its a pale ale....what do you expect?
Bottle. Taste is wheat, corn, hay, grain and water. Pretty much what you would expect from a pale ale.
Enjoyed right from the can. Taste is black licorice, brown sugar, gentle booze and grain. Solid beer from Deep Ellum. Cheers!
On tap at Bristol Brewing. A well balanced, easy drinking oatmeal stout, with a nice balance of oatmeal creaminess and gentle booze kick. Nice.
On tap at Bristol Brewery. Cool place, converted school house. Lightly bitter, smooth drinking IPA.
Bottle in Atlanta. Taste is grain, hay, wheat, light hops and malt. Easy drinking and decent.
I enjoy Samuel Adams beers. I really do. However, in this case I must have gotten an off batch or something. This IPA was skunky, not very hoppy and very bad.
Bottle. Taste is dough, grass, hay, hops, pine and malt. Smooth finish. Well done.
Bottle. Giant pillowy head. Taste is citrus, dough, hops, funk and pine. Balanced and easy drinking.
beer_name: No-Li Expo Series Skyrail Single Hop IPA

review_blob: Bottle. Taste is straw, corn, bitter citrus, hops and hay. Gentle booze finish. Very nice.
